modules.description: Executes AWS requests using Lwt for asynchronous processing, handling authentication and region configuration. It operates on AWS API call structures, input data, and error types specific to AWS operations. Used to perform S3 object uploads, DynamoDB queries, and EC2 instance management within an asynchronous workflow.

Provides functions for constructing and sending HTTP requests to AWS services, parsing JSON responses, and handling authentication signatures. Works with types such as request configurations, HTTP methods, and JSON-encoded data structures. Used to interact with specific AWS services like S3 for object storage or DynamoDB for database operations.

Executes AWS API calls asynchronously using Lwt, managing authentication and region settings. It processes AWS-specific input data, API structures, and error types to perform actions like S3 uploads, DynamoDB queries, and EC2 instance control. Operations are structured around request definitions and response parsing. Examples include uploading files to S3, querying tables in DynamoDB, and starting or stopping EC2 instances.
